Mclash Third-Party Notices

Mclash is an independently developed Android proxy client. Current repository
notices are limited to third-party components that this project downloads,
builds, or packages.

This project may download, build, or package the following third-party
components:

1. mihomo
   Repository: https://github.com/MetaCubeX/mihomo
   License: GPL-3.0
   Usage: The GitHub Actions build resolves the latest stable release, verifies
   the release asset SHA-256 digest, and packages the Android executable as
   libmihomo.so.

2. HevSocks5Tunnel
   Repository: https://github.com/heiher/hev-socks5-tunnel
   License: MIT
   Usage: The GitHub Actions build checks out the pinned HEV_REF, builds the
   Android native library with the Android NDK, and packages
   libhev-socks5-tunnel.so.

3. MetaCubeX meta-rules-dat
   Repository: https://github.com/MetaCubeX/meta-rules-dat
   License: GPL-3.0
   Usage: The GitHub Actions build verifies and packages GeoSite.dat,
   GeoIP.dat, and Country.mmdb so mihomo can initialize without downloading
   geodata when the app starts.

See the corresponding upstream repositories and license files for complete
terms. Build artifacts also include generated license text under the Android
assets directory for packaged native components.
